13/04/2003
BRIJUNI, Croatia -- The seventh meeting of the Bsonia and Herzegovina (BiH)-Croatia interstate council for co-operation -- consisting of the presidency members of the two countries -- was held Saturday (12 April) on the island of Brijuni. 
Acknowledging significant improvement in bilateral relations, the participants stressed the need to settle remaining issues. 
They include signing an agreement on dual citizenship, settling some property and legal problems, and resolving the status of the Ploce port.
On Friday meanwhile, a new border crossing -- Doljani-Metkovic -- opened between BiH and Croatia, providing BiH another link to the Adriatic. 
(RTRS, PBS BiH, HINA, BBC - 12/04/03)
